<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-11-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="371" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d371">
                        <head>371. Telegram 1219 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d371fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/11–1055. Secret;
                                Limit Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>; cleared in draft by
                            Sebald.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-11-12">November 12, 1955, 1:03
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d371-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d371-1"/>
                        <p>1219. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Re your 1135, para. 25, <hi rend="italic">N.Y. Times</hi> article
                            November 8 could not RPT not have been based on any responsible U.S.
                            official source. We have no indication as to origin, although internal
                            evidence points strongly to <hi rend="italic">Daily Worker</hi> article
                            as chief inspiration.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HH_1"><hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>